  </head>

  <body class="portfolio-details-page">
    <Navbar />

    <main class="main">
      <!-- Page Title -->
      <div class="page-title accent-background">
        <div class="container">
          <h1>Bookstop</h1>
          <nav class="breadcrumbs">
            <ol>
              <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
              <li><a href="/Projects">Projects</a></li>
              <li><a href="/Dify">Dify Projects</a></li>
              <li class="current">Bookstop</li>
            </ol>
          </nav>
        </div>
      </div><!-- End Page Title -->

      <!-- Portfolio Details Section -->
      <section id="portfolio-details" class="portfolio-details section">
        <div class="container" data-aos="fade-up">
          <div class="portfolio-details-slider swiper init-swiper">
            <script type="application/json" class="swiper-config">
              {
                "loop": true,
                "speed": 600,
                "autoplay": {
                  "delay": 5000
                },
                "slidesPerView": "auto",
                "navigation": {
                  "nextEl": ".swiper-button-next",
                  "prevEl": ".swiper-button-prev"
                },
                "pagination": {
                  "el": ".swiper-pagination",
                  "type": "bullets",
                  "clickable": true
                }
              }
            </script>
            <div class="swiper-wrapper align-items-center">
              <div class="swiper-slide">
                <img src="/assets/img/dify/bookstop/bookstopdify.png" alt="" />
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="swiper-button-prev"></div>
            <div class="swiper-button-next"></div>
            <div class="swiper-pagination"></div>
          </div>

          <div class="row justify-content-between gy-4 mt-4">
            <div class="col-lg-8" data-aos="fade-up">
              <div class="portfolio-description">
                <h2>Overview</h2>
                <p>
                  Bookstop is your go-to Cloudstaff platform for exploring and
                  borrowing books with ease. With the Bookstop chatbot, you get
                  a friendly companion to guide you through your browsing
                  experience, offering personalized help and seamless
                  communication to make every visit a delight.
                </p>
                <div class="row align-items-center">
                  <div class="col-md-6 d-flex justify-content-center">
                    <img
                      src="/assets/img/dify/bookstop/bookstop1.png"
                      class="img-fluid zoomable-image"
                      style="max-width: 80%; height: auto; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; cursor: pointer;"
                      data-bs-toggle="modal"
                      data-bs-target="#imageModal"
                      onclick="setModalImage(this.src, this.alt)"
                    />
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h3>Book Recommendation</h3>
                    <p>
                      The Bookstop chatbot intelligently recommends books based
                      on user queries, preferences, or previous interactions. It
                      analyzes keywords and topics of interest to suggest titles
                      from the Cloudstaff library's knowledge base. Whether
                      you're looking for a new genre or continuing a series, the
                      chatbot curates options tailored to your needs.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="row align-items-center">
                  <div
                    class="col-md-6 order-md-2 d-flex justify-content-center"
                  >
                    <img
                      src="/assets/img/dify/bookstop/bookstop2.png"
                      class="img-fluid zoomable-image"
                      style="max-width: 80%; height: auto; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; cursor: pointer;"
                      data-bs-toggle="modal"
                      data-bs-target="#imageModal"
                      onclick="setModalImage(this.src, this.alt)"
                    />
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-md-6 order-md-1">
                    <h3>Book Availability & Comparison</h3>
                    <p>
                      Users can ask the chatbot if a specific book is currently
                      available in the library catalog. If multiple books match
                      the query, the chatbot can compare titles based on author,
                      genre, and publication year. This helps users make
                      informed choices before deciding which book to borrow.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="row align-items-center">
                  <div class="col-md-6 d-flex justify-content-center">
                    <img
                      src="/assets/img/dify/bookstop/bookstop3.png"
                      class="img-fluid zoomable-image"
                      style="max-width: 80%; height: auto; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; cursor: pointer;"
                      data-bs-toggle="modal"
                      data-bs-target="#imageModal"
                      onclick="setModalImage(this.src, this.alt)"
                    />
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h3>Saving & Viewing Saved Books</h3>
                    <p>
                      The chatbot allows users to save interesting titles during
                      their search or conversation. These saved books can be
                      easily accessed later, enabling a seamless return to
                      potential reads. It's a convenient way to build a reading
                      list without losing track of your picks.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="row align-items-center">
                  <div
                    class="col-md-6 order-md-2 d-flex justify-content-center"
                  >
                    <img
                      src="/assets/img/dify/bookstop/bookstop4.png"
                      class="img-fluid zoomable-image"
                      style="max-width: 80%; height: auto; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; cursor: pointer;"
                      data-bs-toggle="modal"
                      data-bs-target="#imageModal"
                      onclick="setModalImage(this.src, this.alt)"
                    />
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-md-6 order-md-1">
                    <h3>Borrowing Information</h3>
                    <p>
                      When a user wishes to borrow a book, the chatbot provides
                      details such as borrowing limits, return deadlines, and
                      current status. It guides the user through the borrowing
                      process and answers related policy questions. This ensures
                      users understand how to check out and return materials
                      properly.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="row align-items-center">
                  <div class="col-md-6 d-flex justify-content-center">
                    <img
                      src="/assets/img/dify/bookstop/bookstop5.png"
                      class="img-fluid zoomable-image"
                      style="max-width: 80%; height: auto; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; cursor: pointer;"
                      data-bs-toggle="modal"
                      data-bs-target="#imageModal"
                      onclick="setModalImage(this.src, this.alt)"
                    />
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h3>Popularity Ratings</h3>
                    <p>
                      The chatbot can show popularity ratings based on user
                      engagement or internal metrics from the library system.
                      These ratings help highlight trending or highly
                      recommended books among the Cloudstaff community. It’s a
                      useful tool for discovering books that others have found
                      valuable or enjoyable.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-3" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
              <div class="portfolio-info sticky">
                <h3>Project Information</h3>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Developer</strong> The Whole Team</li>
                  <li><strong>Technology</strong> Dify.ai</li>
                  <li>
                    <a
                      href="/docs/Chatbot Handover Document 1.pdf"
                      class="btn-visit align-self-start"
                      download>Handover Document</a>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section><!-- /Portfolio Details Section -->
    </main>

    <Footer />
    <Modal />

    <!-- Scroll Top -->
    <a
      href="#"
      id="scroll-top"
      class="scroll-top d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
      ><i class="bi bi-arrow-up-short"></i></a
    >

    <!-- Preloader -->
    <div id="preloader"></div>

    <!-- Vendor JS Files -->
    <script is:inline src="/assets/vendor/bootstrap/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"
    ></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/vendor/php-email-form/validate.js"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/vendor/aos/aos.js"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/vendor/purecounter/purecounter_vanilla.js"
    ></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/vendor/glightbox/js/glightbox.min.js"
    ></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/vendor/swiper/swiper-bundle.min.js"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/vendor/imagesloaded/imagesloaded.pkgd.min.js"
    ></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/vendor/isotope-layout/isotope.pkgd.min.js"
    ></script>

    <!-- Main JS File -->
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/main.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
